SIMPLE: mistrust
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mistrust
<hw>Mis*trust"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Want of confidence
or trust; suspicion; distrust.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mistrust</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mistrust
<hw>Mis*trust"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To regard with
jealousy or suspicion; to suspect; to doubt the integrity of; to
distrust.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will never <qex>mistrust</qex> my wife again.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To forebode as near, or likely to occur; to
surmise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>By a divine instinct, men's minds <qex>mistrust</qex>⟦br⟧
Ensuing dangers.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mistruster</ent>⟦br⟧
